The '''Anti Common Market and Free Trade Party''' was a British political party that opposed Britain's membership of the European Union and fought a number of [[by-elections]] in the 1970s and 1980s.<ref>http://www.angelfire.com/apes/burning-icicles/british_politics.html</ref> It was also known as the '''Free Trade Liberal Party''' and '''All Party Anti-Common Market'''. Among its members were [[Arthur Seldon]] and [[Oliver Smedley]]. It saw itself in the [[Liberal Party (UK)|Liberal Party]] tradition and its members were often involved with the free market [[Institute of Economic Affairs]].
