'''Dalit Kisan Dal''' (Dalit Peasants Party), is a [[political party]] in [[Punjab, India|Punjab]], [[India]]. The party was formed as a splinter group from [[Lok Bhalai Party]] 2001, when activists from LBP in [[Khamano]], [[Machhiwara]], [[Ropar]] and [[Samrala]] broke away. As of 2001 the general secretary of DKD was Bhinder Singh Ranwan, and the party president was Iqbal Singh Kapurthala. The party claims to fight for better conditions for peasants and [[dalit (outcaste)|dalit]]s.<ref>''The Tribune''. ''[http://www.tribuneindia.com/2001/20010304/ldh1.htm Workers quit Lok Bhalai Party]''</ref>

